args:
After a fierce battle with Seimei, Luca emerges
the winner, but he returns the prize mirror to
Seimei, claiming only the cash purse. In thanks,
Seimei holds a grand New Year's feast and the
crowd enjoys the belated year-end revels.
We've come to the final showdown, folks!\nWin or lose, our fighters' dreams end here!
Give him the ol' sylvan one-two, Luca!
Neither fighter is budging an inch as this\nbattle reaches fever pitch! Which of our\ntwo combatants will carry the day?!
These guys are INTENSE! They've been\ngoing full-tilt since the round started.
They both have something they refuse to\nrelinquish. Still, such a clash must be\nwearing them down quickly.
True. This stalemate won't last long.\nBoth of them have to be reaching a\nbreaking point.
Uh-oh! It looks like both of them\nare showing signs of slowing down.\nThis could be the decisive moment, folks!
Indeed it is.\nThis match ends now...in my victory!
I'll wring out every last drop of power I\nhave. Dragon's pulse, coursing through the\nearth below! Open wide your rocky maw!
No! Seimei aims to use up all he has left\nhere and now. You have to dodge it, Luca!
You put up an amazing fight, Luca...\nThe elder's going to be thrilled to hear.
Easy there.\nYou make it sound like I already lost!
Whâ€”this is incredible! It looked like he\ntook the blow head-on, but as the smoke\nclears, Luca stands strong! He's still in it!
Heh heh. Sorry, Seimei.\nLooks like I win this endurance match!
What? HOW?! Lord Seimei's attack landed!\nHow is his opponent still conscious?

Tch. Elemental nullification out of
sheer dumb luck. He called upon wind,
which in turn quelled the resonance of
my earth spell.
Yeah, no idea what you just said, but it\nwasn't luck: I planned it! I knew it was a\nlong shot, but I'm still movin', baby!
Now, let's finish this for real.\nHAAAAAAAH!
Seimei's attacks were incredible,\nthough. My heart's still pounding!
*sigh* Fine. A loss is a loss.\nAs the host of this tournament,\nI'm obliged to crown its winner.
Kuzunoha, fetch Yura's reflecting mirror\nand the prize money. Let's get this award\nceremony over with.
In commemoration of your victory,\nAmaterasu offers you this boon.\nCongratulations.
Right, uh... Thanks. So, this is the mirror\nthat reflects the viewer's memories, huh?
With this, I'd be able to keep my memories\nof the elder, no matter what happens to\nhim. Still... Hm.
I want you to keep this.

Do I have pudding in my ears, or did he
say what I think he just said? But why,
Luca? That mirror was the whole reason
you even entered this tournament thingie!
I mean, yeah, but...\nWhat Seimei said got me thinking.
And ultimately, I decided he should be\nthe one to keep it.
I only just found out about the thing.\nPlus, unlike Seimei's grandfather,\nmy elder's still alive.
So I figure, why don't I just use the money\nto nosh on some good food with him and\nrack up the memories while I still can?
Tell me something I don't know, buddy.\nThough that's pretty rich, coming from the\nguy who snuck into his own tournament.
But there was a reason you did it...\nThis mirror. Now will you hurry up and\ntake the dang thing already?
*sigh* I suspect you won't budge an inch\nuntil I do. Then yes, I most humbly accept.
But I will not be indebted to you for this.\nThus, I have a demand of my own.
Some time after the tournament's end,\nat the Halidom...
Dude, YUM-O! The grub at this\nNew Year's feast is a-ma-zing!
You're giving me deja vu, Luca.
Hey, when the food's this good, you've\ngotta shout it from the rooftops, okay?\nNow, you want in on this mochi, Notte?
Does a faerie flap in the woods?\nLemme sink my teeth into that baby!
Glad you two are having fun.\nIt really was kind of you to throw\nthis all together for us, Seimei.
Think nothing of it. Any less after being\ngifted that mirror would be a stain on\nmy good name as Wyrmclan leader.
There're plenty of goodies left to eat,\nso keep tuckin' in, folks! Enjoy!
Oh, I intend to. The orphanage children\nare having an eating contest, and I plan\nto destroy them. Lovingly, of course.
That reminds meâ€”how are things looking\nthere, money-wise? Any better?
Yes, thanks to you. Struggles still lie\nahead, but they have a fair bit more\nbreathing room now.

Good. On my end, the elder's gone and
perked right up. The villagers apparently
went and gave him a full dramatic
reenactment of the tournament.
Looks like I've got plenty of time to go\nspread New Year's cheer and make all\nsortsa good memories with him.
And it's all thanks to our ol' pal Seimei.\nKinda. Sorta. Even if he won't admit it.
It's simply good fortune at work.\nThough I admit it does feel nice to see\nthat I've done my job in spreading it.
After all, it's my duty to educate the world\nabout Hinomoto's superlative culture.
Everything fell behind schedule this year\nafter all that nonsense with Doman, so it's\na relief to know we got there in the end.
I'm sure. Thank you for helping us ring in\nanother splendid New Year's, Seimei.
Yes. What she said. And that reminds me:\nit's a bit far into the new year for this, but\ncan we still offer the customary greeting?
I have no objection.\nYou can do the honors.
Wonderful. Then, on three, everyone.\nOne... Two...
Let's make it another good one, people!
